                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.01A/181a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-08T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>207. You should take the earliest opportunity to impress upon Prime Minister and
                    other officials the great importance of an unreservedly cooperative attitude on
                    the part of all Iranian Government officials toward the various American
                    advisers now in process of selection. Please make it clear that in our view it
                    will be worse than useless to employ these men unless all concerned are prepared
                    to further their efforts to the utmost. You may further say that this Government
                    will hardly feel justified in continuing its efforts to provide advisers unless
                    it can be assured that the Iranian Government shares this viewpoint. In this
                    connection, we regard the choice of Minister of Finance and the proposed
                    Minister of Food as particularly important, since those officials will be the
                    determining factor in the success or failure of the Financial and Food and
                    Supply advisers, who will form the keystone of the whole advisory set-up.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
